Introduction

Riina is a South Korean singer signed with Grandline Group. She is a member of the girl group H1-KEY and a former member of the pre-debut trainee team WM Ggumnamu.

In 2018, she appeared as a contestant on the survival show Produce 48 where she represented WM Entertainment. She was eliminated in episode 5 after ranking 73rd place.

She debuted as a member of H1-KEY on January 5, 2022, with their first single "Athletic Girl".

In 2023, she appeared as a contestant in Mnet's survival show, "Queendom Puzzle". On August 8, it was revealed that Riina was eliminated in the semi-final, her final rank being 18th.
